tspan.tspan: Temporal trends in overlap metrics.
Each panel represents a different overlap metric. The color of
the fill represents the temporal correlation of the overlap metric for that spatial cell through time. Negative
(blue) values reflect declines in the metric through time. Positive values (red) reflect increases in the
overlap metric through time. The following description are taken from Carroll et al. (2019).
Asymetric alpha:
Measures the competitive pressure of predator on prey
Local colocation:
Measures co‐occurrence by estimating the correlation of predator and prey densities
Biomass-weighted overlap:
Measures amount of predator biomass interacting with prey (scaled to
maximum prey density)
Hurlbert's overlap:
Measures interspecific encounter rate between predator and prey
Schoener's D:
Measures how equally predator and prey use space relative to its availability
Bhattacharyya's coefficient:
Measures statistical affinity between two distributions
AB ratio:
Measures predator production that can be attributed to spatial overlap with prey
